        {
          "username": "Doc Soulshine",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "105418174038586305810",
          "user_review_count": 3,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLIEje9NHRAiEypn5ncENkiuYJ14s4XD8MurZcijx-CSw6Znw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "They deserve only one star for their after care team.  I had a patient who had a fairly routine blood test done there and couldn't access her results in the portal.  When she called the after care team for the results, she spoke to a CityMD after care team member who identified himself as 'JOHN G.'  John G was shockingly incompetent.  First, he gave her incorrect results (keep in mind this is very simple bloodwork - a simple yes or no was all was needed); then he told her there was \"an extra, highly sensitive finding\" that he couldn't give out over the phone, terrifying her and, by extension, me, and told her she had to go physically to CityMD on 37th Street.  She left work in a panic, thinking something terrible had been revealed because of John G's alarming and unhelpful words, and was told in office they could do nothing for her but call the same after care team.  The office staff put her on the phone with a different rep from the same after care team.  This 2nd person also confused the results, reading them backwards, but finally reported them correctly after intensive questioning - the same results already in the patient's online portal.  The 2nd rep said she did not know why John G would have made alarming statements about an \"extra\" \"highly sensitive\" or \"secret finding.\"  This is appallingly poor bedside manner and also reeks of incompetence.  John G should be fired or, at a bare minimum, put on leave until he can successfully complete additional training.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25oSVdXSnRMVTVTZWtadU5rVnFNbFZRYVc5SVQyYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x31f7491ebbf8773b!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOnhIWWJtLU5SekZuNkVqMlVQaW9IT2c%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "11 months ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2025-07-24T17:45:28+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Jennifer Henkin",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "109740267549057668318",
          "user_review_count": 11,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWm-dGUTQciF3VU1G9MIkLyFs5HLuxQI1Og2gdbbgbCuBtE73Ielg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "I have been coming to this location for about 5 years. I\u2019ve never been uncomfortable until today when I had the displeasure of meeting Dr. Mithani (blue haired provider). I would like to preface that I\u2019m a surgeon and know how an exam should be performed. She did not examine me. She checked my lungs but that was it. She did not check my throat, palpate my sinuses, look for a cause for my issue.  She did not do a full head and neck exam. My rapid Covid/flu was negative and she didn\u2019t seem to care about helping me with the symptoms I\u2019ve been dealing with.\nI have been sick for a week and after doing all the things I know how to do I needed someone to make sure I wasn\u2019t missing anything. She was curt and was dismissive with my questions. I have a cough that has been keeping me up all night for the last week and I had to ask HER to send me cough medicine. She wasn\u2019t going to send it. Her only \u201cadvice\u201d was to use my inhaler as needed. Thanks so much for your expertise.  If you work in an urgent care you should show some care/empathy for the patients that come to see you. If I treated my patients that way they most definitely would not come back. If I have to go back I will ask to see a different provider or just change locations.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTUN3OHFicVhBEAE!2m1!1s0x0:0x31f7491ebbf8773b!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgMCw8qbqXA%7C%7C?hl=en",
